eople. It also examines the ways in which the allied arts are mediated by institutions and the fragility of craft commissions once considered an integral part of the built environment. Considering a wide range of craftspeople, materials, and forms - from the ceramics of Jack Sures and Jordi Bonnet to the textile work of Mariette Rousseau Vermette and Carole Sabiston - Alfoldy celebrates the successes of architectural craftsmanship. The first work of its kind, The Allied Arts develops ideas about the complex relationship between architecture and craft that reach well beyond national boundaries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aArchitecturezCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aDecorative artszCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aHandicraftzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 7aARCHITECTURE / History / Contemporary (1945-).2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077358682640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773586826423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773586826/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles